                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- A piece of white paper with the title of the Ms. ,ዳዊት, written in blue ink is glued onto the front cover of the Ms. - The Pss. are divided into groups of ten separated by a line of alternating black and red dots. - Numerous glosses and ʾandǝmta-commentaries, in Amharic. - Notes in the margin, not clearly visible: <locus target="#1r">fol.  1r</locus>. - Note in the margin exemplifying Saul, Shimei the son of Gera, Absalom and Ahithophel as ungodly people: <locus target="#11r">fol.  11r</locus>. - Crude notes: fols. 67v, 110r, 123r. - Part of Ethiopic syllabary, crudely written: <locus target="#159v">fol.  159v</locus>.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
